	<str name="Title">
		SOIL REMEDIATION
	</str>
	<str name="Abstract">
		Soil contaminated with contaminants such as a heavy hydrocarbon or a chlorinated hydrocarbon is cleaned, preferably on-site, by excavating the contaminated soil (126), suspending it in aqueous media, preferably containing a super-surfactant such as the micellar surfactant formed by sonicating polar substituted heavy hydrocarbon in the presence of an alkali metal salt such as sodium silicate and sonicating the suspension. At least 85 % of the contaminant is removed from the soil including fine particles having a particle size below about 70 microns. The soil cleaning can be conducted in an apparatus including a mixer (108) for forming the slurry, and inclined trough (104) having transducers (114) within the trough for cleaning the slurry and a separator tank (106) for separating an upper oily layer, solids and fines.
	</str>
